title: Software Engineer
post: Entry, mid, and senior-level, positions (multiple available) to develop software for tactical reconnaissance applications.  Candidates should possess familiarity in one or more of the following areas: software design, signal processing, GPU processing, graphics, sensor data fusion, image data visualization, and database design.

title: Website Assistant - Data Entry & Imaging
post: Looking for someone who enjoys learning about new products, entering their specs into large spreadsheets and then adding and editing the photos that go with them. We will teach you everything, but a background in Excel and Photoshop will make it a faster process.

title: Back End Developer
post: PIEtechSM located in Powhatan, VA, is the developer of MoneyGuidePro financial planning software which is designed for financial advisors. As an industry leader in innovation, we believe in providing advisors software that is smart, easy and adaptable to create friendly and meaningful goal-based financial plans for their clients. MoneyGuidePro is used by thousands of financial service professionals from small-size planning firms to large financial institutions. We strive daily to create great software and provide superior customer support to our users. For the past five years, MoneyGuidePro has been recognized in Financial Planning Magazine as the #1 software of choice among financial advisors.

title: Junior Software Developer
post: We are seeking a Junior Software Developer with a focus on front-end development in Javascript to join the InsuranceMenu team. As a Junior Software Developer you will be working on our agile team to build / enhance the web front end, as well as learning server side code in Java/Groovy, SQL. As we are a growing startup you will have the ability to learn a wide range of technologies and work your way towards taking a large responsibility in the software and product development life cycle that will drive InsuranceMenu to continued success.

title: Software Developer
post: Become proficient with the Clarion (softvelocity.com) programming language. Develop software to continue to grow and update our current software packages as well as develop new custom software packages in the future. Deal with software testing for any minor or major updates to all software packages. Be involved with building install packages and deployment of updates to customers. Create tech support websites and keep information current.

title: Front-End Software Engineer
post: New Relic is looking for a creative, forward-thinking front end engineer to join our Alerts Interfaces engineering team. You will work with some of the best engineers and take on some of the most complex problems in the industry. We are responsible for Javascript, Ruby and Java services designed to give our customers confidence in the their systems' continuing health by providing timely, accurate, and context rich user configured alerts and incident management workflows so they can quickly understand and act on alert initiated incidents. Over the next year we will be focused on modernizing our UI, building new features, and collaborating with the other platform products to ensure UX consistency and enable Alerts to consume reusable UI components.
